    <text id="B0518T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>How proposes to convert an engine seized from the Confederate government into use
                    with a saw mill to provide employment and lumber in the region.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau <abbr expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">R. F. &amp; A.
                        L.</abbr><lb/><abbr expan="Headquarters">HdQrs</abbr> Sixth District <abbr
                            expan="Virginia">Va</abbr>
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Colonel">Col.</abbr> O. Brown<lb/><abbr
                            expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst. Comr.</abbr> Richmond, <abbr
                            expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1865-08-07"><abbr expan="August">Augt</abbr> 7t 1865</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Colonel</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I have the honor to state that there is at this place a portable steam engine of
                    about (10) ten horse power that belonged to the so called Confederate <abbr
                        expan="Government">Govt</abbr>. I am of opinion that it can be put in
                    working order for less than ($100.00) one hundred dollars, and learning that
                    there is at Fort Monroe and Portsmouth a Saw Mill not in use, together with
                    parts of Machinery that would reduce the cost to almost fifty dollars. I propose
                    to set a Saw Mill in operation as by so doing, Lumber that will certainly be
                    needed can be furnished, and employment given to freedmen who will require it.
                    Will you please give the order necessary for the transfer of the Saw Mill
                    &amp;c to me</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>I am, Colonel<lb/>Very Respectfully</salute>
                    <signed>W. Storer How, <abbr expan="Captain and Assistant Quartermaster">Capt
                            &amp; AQM</abbr><lb/><abbr expan="Superintendent">Supt</abbr> 6th
                            <abbr expan="District">Dist</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
